<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-04-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-04-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="960" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d960">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/7011.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-04-05">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 5, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>171. The Department assumes that such action as you have taken on your
                            own initiative in regard to General Angeles, as reported in your April
                            4, 1 p.m., is based solely on humanitarian grounds and is entirely
                            informal and unofficial.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>